Objective:

Explore basic properties and structure and synthesis of biomaterials to integrate the concepts of material science, biology and chemistry.
Critically examine basic surface and compatible characterization of biomaterials currently utilized in specific biomedical tissue. 
Probe nanotechnology for biomaterials applications in drug-delivery, biosensor and tissue engineering.


COURSE Topics:

General Introduction of Nano-Biomaterials 
Introduction to nanotechnology
Basic Materials properties and surface analysis 
Structure, properties and application of Materials
   
